Rating: 4
This is a terrific soup, not at all bland (though I did add garlic). And a heartier broth would overwhelm the lamb, I think. I made the broth the day before so I could skim the fat off the next day, added carrots to the onions in the second step just to get more veggies in (and the resulting color was an added bonus). No need to brown the meat first, as some reviewers did; the recipe does not require it and adding that step makes it a less attractive recipe from a time standpoint. I also did not strain the broth, I like the vegetables. But properly salted and peppered, the broth is sublime. And the combination of the lamb, veggies, and orzo is terrific. This is a keeper.

Rating: 4
I added garlic when I sauteed the onion

Rating: 4
This is a fantastic soup. Incredibly tasty and super easy to make. Instead of orzo I used bulgur wheat the first time and pearl barley the second time (they are healthier), otherwise kept the exact recipe (used frozen spinach). Both versions are great. I think the soup is better the next day. I could eat this for breakfast, lunch and dinner. One of my favorite recipes ever.

