Rating: 3
I liked the idea of the soup, but modified the technique by first browning the lamb shanks in olive oil. Removed the shanks; sauteed the vegetables (added plenty of garlic) until softened. Then, added all of the liquid and the lamb and proceeded with recipe. Substituted arugula for the spinach.

Rating: 2
I had boned a leg of lamb, and used the bones like it was a shank. It worked out very nicely. It was a rich and tasty soup - after I remembered to add the aslt.

Rating: 4
Excellent soup. In the interest of a little more heartiness which I like I made a few changes. I minced the "broth" vegetables, adding a few cloves of minced garlic (what are lamb shanks without garlic) and a large onion (minced), sauted them until soft and then continued with the recipe. I also substituted beef broth for half the water. I did not strain the broth and did not add the onion at the end. I used a little extra spinach AND let the whole thing sit overnight before reheating and serving. It got rave review at a dinner party.

Rating: 1
This is a bland tasting dish and does not have the hardy flavor one would like in a meat stock soup. I would find a better recipe to use my lamb shanks in next time.

